Welcome to the wonderful world of MemNotify!

Frequently asked questions (FAQ):

1. What is memnotify?

MemNotify is a library to manage memory usage signals, mostly from cgroups containers.
For more detailed description and examples see the "Design Notes" in file doc/design.txt

2. What for that is?

To control how much memory used in embedded system and react properly e.g. by not
handling every malloc() to be successful.

3. Do you have something Qt-less?

Yes, see libmemnotify.